</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/> sacrilegious and  accursed <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/> and grave-robbers <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>l. 1 is from the funerary curse upon those who disturb the tomb; l. 2 is not from any of the standard formulae. Could there be a use of <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀνόσιοι</foreign> to those cursed?</p>
         </div>
